source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Summarize disk usage of each file, showing shared extents

For each path, prints three columns:

Total      — logical bytes used by non-inline extents Exclusive  — bytes not
shared with any other file Set shared — (top-level only) physical bytes shared
within this subtree

Usage: du [OPTIONS] <PATHS>...

Arguments:
  <PATHS>...
          One or more files or directories to summarize

Options:
  -s, --summarize
          Display only a total for each argument, not per-file lines

      --raw
          Show raw numbers in bytes

      --human-readable
          Show human-friendly numbers using base 1024 (default)

      --iec
          Use 1024 as a base (KiB, MiB, GiB, TiB)

      --si
          Use 1000 as a base (kB, MB, GB, TB)

      --kbytes
          Show sizes in KiB, or kB with --si

      --mbytes
          Show sizes in MiB, or MB with --si

      --gbytes
          Show sizes in GiB, or GB with --si

      --tbytes
          Show sizes in TiB, or TB with --si

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
